title: For Trade:  Honady 9mm HAP Bullets 115gr  .355 Diameter
postcontent:
These are excellent bullets for competition shooting and personal defense.  In fact, its the most accurate bullet I ever shot. (see below).

Hornady Action Pistol Bullets (HAP) are engineered with the competitive shooter in mind. Hornady began with a bullet legendary in its accuracy - the Hornady  XTP - and redesigned it as the perfect competition projectile. While the XTP uses folds and a cannelure to aid in expansion and increase terminal performance, expansion is meaningless in competition. So, the folds and cannelure are gone from the HAP bullet. 

 Because jamming can cost a competitive shooter the match, Hornady placed the HAP's pure lead core inside a copper jacket that protects the nose, ensuring smooth feeding. And like the XTP, the core of the HAP bullet is cold swaged from pure lead to give it amazing consistency, balance and stability in flight.



Will ship out of state.

title: For Sale:  Springfield Armory M1A National Match
postcontent:
For sale is an excellent condition Springfield Armory M1A National Match, complete with original hard case and paperwork. I am the original owner; the rifle was purchased brand new several months ago and has had only 216 rounds through it since new. The rifle is in excellent condition with no visible detractions. This rifle has the NM walnut stock with the 22" parkerized carbon steel barrel.

The National Match incorporates an array of upgrades from Springfield Armory to insure this rifle will outshoot any standard M1A. Those upgrades include the NM medium weight barrel, the NM walnut stock which has been epoxy bedded to the barreled action, NM trigger group (measured at 4.5lbs), NM full hooded rear sight, NM front sight, as well as the NM gas system (unitized). This particular rifle shoots Federal Gold Medal Match very well and I am sure the avid reloader could develop a load to shoot even better. The rifle has always been  meticulously maintained with the proper care given (using a bore guide and chamber port). The rifle did wear a scope mount previously which mandated the removal of the stripper clip guide; the stripper clip guide has been reinstalled however the roll pin securing it in place has not been installed due to the next owners potential desire to remove it (if a scope mount is again desired). If the next owner chooses to remove the stripper clip guide all that is needed is a soft-tipped hammer to tap it out. 

Included with the rifle is the original hard case, all original paperwork, and (1) 10 round magazine.
